      <memberdef kind="function" id="group___window_stack_1ga44a239d564b96ca93a149a29d89707d1" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>bool</type>
        <definition>bool window_stack_remove</definition>
        <argsstring>(Window *window, bool animated)</argsstring>
        <name>window_stack_remove</name>
        <param>
          <type>Window *</type>
          <declname>window</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>bool</type>
          <declname>animated</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Removes a given window from the window stack that belongs to the app task. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>If there are no windows for the app left on the stack, the app will be killed by the system, shortly. To avoid this, make sure to push another window shortly after or before removing the last window. </para>
</simplesect>
<parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>window</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The window to remove. If the window is NULL or if it is not on the stack, this function is a no-op. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>animated</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pass in <computeroutput>true</computeroutput> to animate the removal of the window using a side-to-side sliding animation to reveal the next window. This is only used in case the window happens to be on top of the window stack (thus visible). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>True if window was successfully removed, false otherwise. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
